snippet: In what separatist officials call the “Ukrainianization” of the leadership, almost all the original Russian leaders of the rebellion have resigned and gone home, replaced by Ukrainians of dubious qualifications.
abstract: Setbacks suffered by Russian-backed separatists in Ukraine has led to so-called 'Ukrainianization' of their leadership, with almost all the original Russian leaders resigning and going home, replaced by Ukrainians of dubious qualifications; change has opened prospect of peace talks, but has also left rebel military ranks adrift.
lead_paragraph: In what separatist officials call the “Ukrainianization” of the leadership, almost all the original Russian leaders of the rebellion have resigned and gone home, replaced by Ukrainians of dubious qualifications.

headline.main: Plenty of Room at the Top of Ukraine’s Fading Rebellion
